text:
My go-to prata place around pasir panjang/telok blangah area, whenever I had late dinner or supper :) just try it!

Posted the menu for references :)

Kopi very nice, staff very friendly and keep cleaning the tables and mop e floor.
Had briyani n roti john, not bad, will sure come back!

Table n chair not oily or sticky like other mamak stalls, i really like this place

I used to visit the restaurant quite often. Lately their food quality is on the decline. Maybe the cooks had been changed. I had masala Dosa I I was quite disappointed..the dosa was not hot or crispy. The masala is ok. The coconut chutney is cold like that taken out from fidge. The bru coffee is light and the flavor is less. The drink maker also had changed too. They had to improve the quality of the food.
Service is excellent as ever with very nice staffs. the food is very good and the drinks are very good as well. Go for the susu halia its very tasty

I ordered the Mee Goreng with chicken meat for $7. It was a big plate, and the amount of chicken meat was probably the most I've ever encountered in a plate of Mee Goreng. Overall, the taste was good, and the price was fair.
